               <msContents>
                  <summary>Sword of the Trinity, ሠይፈ፡ ሥላሴ፡, Journey to Heaven, Blessing of Abunä Yared, History of Priest Yared, Wise of the Wise, Booklet of prayer that came down from heaven for a nobleman in the land of the Afrəgi, Prayer of the Twelve Disciples, Prayer of the Disciples for Forgiveness of Sin, Sword of Divinity, ሠይፈ፡ መለኮት፡, Mystagogia, ትምህርተ፡ ኅቡዓት፡, God of the Luminaries, እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘብርሃናት፡, Prayer: I take refuge, ተማኅፀንኩ፡</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>

                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="5r"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT2286ZenaSellase"/>
                  </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                      <locus from="5r" to="8r"/>
                      <locus from="10r" to="15r"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT1873Mangad"/>
                  </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <locus from="15v"/>
                      <title>Blessing of Abunä Yared, <persName ref="PRS10245Yared"/>
                     </title>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        ቡራኬ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ያሬድ፡ ዘይትበሀል፡ ለለዕለቱ፡ ስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘፈጠረ፡ ሰማያተ፡ ወምድረ፡ ኪነ፡ ወተግባረ፡...
                      </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <locus from="16r" to="18v"/>
                      <title>History of Priest Yared, <persName ref="PRS10245Yared"/>
                     </title>
                      <note>This story, which is slightly different from what is in his <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገድል፡</foreign>, is composed in Amharic, but the beginning is in Gə‘əz</note>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        ዝታሪክ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ያሬድ፡ ባሕታዊ፡ ወድንግል፡ ዘይነግር፡ ኵነቶ፡ ፅንሰቶ፡ ወልደቶ፡...ያሬድ፡ በተወለደል፡ በ፯፡ ዓመቱ፡...
                      </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                     <locus from="19r" to="49r"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT2296Sayfas"/>
                      <note>
                        Arranged for the days of the week (
                        Monday, <locus target="#19r"/>;
                        Tuesday, <locus target="#22v"/>;
                        Wednesday, <locus target="#27v"/>;
                        Thursday, <locus target="#31v"/>;
                        Friday, <locus target="#36r"/>;
                        Saturday, <locus target="#41v"/>;
                        Sunday, <locus target="#45v"/>)</note>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i6">
                     <locus from="49r" to="64r"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT2393tabiba"/>
                      <note>
                        Arranged for the days of the week (
                        Monday, <locus target="#107r"/>;
                        Tuesday, <locus target="#109v"/>;
                        Wednesday, <locus target="#111r"/>;
                        Thursday, <locus target="#112v"/>;
                        Friday, <locus target="#113v"/>;
                        Saturday, <locus target="#114v"/>;
                        Sunday, <locus target="#116r"/>)
                      </note>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        እግዚብሔር፡ ጥበበ፡ ጠቢባን።ሐሓሊ። እስከ፡ ለዓለም፡ እምጥንት፡ እንት፡ ኢትበሊ፡...
                      </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i7">
                     <locus from="64r" to="76v"/>
                      <title>Booklet of prayer that came down from heaven for a nobleman in the land of the Afrəgi</title>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        በስመ፡ አብ፡...ኦእግዚእየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዕቀበኒ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ሎቱ፡ ስብሐት፡ በእንተ፡ ዘኃደርከ፡ በከርሠ፡ ማርያም፡...ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ከመዝ፡ ምጽአታ፡ እስመ፡ ነገረ፡ ፩፡ መኰንን፡ በሀገረ፡ አፍርንጊ፡...
                      </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i8">
                     <locus from="76v" to="90r"/>
                      <title type="complete" ref="LIT3942ArdeetCh"/>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        በስመ፡ አብ፡...ጸሎተ፡ ዘ፲ወ፪አርድእት፡ ዘወሀቦሙ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አመ፡ የዓርግ፡ ሰማየ፡ በዘይድኅኑ፡ እምኃጢአት፡ ወእምኵሉ፡
                        ሕማመ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወበፍስ፡ ወእምኵሉ፡ ፀራዊ፡ ወሕምዘ፡ አርዌ፡ ምድር፡ ወእምኵሉ፡ ዘቦቱ፡ ሕምዝ፡ ዘይቀትል፡ ወእምኵሉ፡ ሕማም፡ ወድካም፡...
                        በኢያሄ፡ ስምከ፡ ግሩም፡ በሱራሄ፡ ስምከ፡ ዓቢት፡...
                      </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i9">
                     <locus from="90r" to="93r"/>
                      <title>Prayer of the Disciples for forgiveness of sin, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ ስርየተ፡ ኃጢአት፡</foreign>
                     </title>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        ጸሎት፡ ስርየተ፡ ኃቲአት፡ ዘሰአሉ፡ ሐዋርያ፤ ኦእግዚኦ፡ እግዚእየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ መሐሪ፡ ወመስተሣህል፡...ስረይ፡ ኃጢአትየ፡...በሴቃ፡ ወበጼቃ፡ ስምከ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ርድአኒ፡...ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ኢተጽሕፈት፡ በእደ፡ ሰብእ፡ አላ፡ ለሊሁ፡ መድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘጸሐፋ፡ በእዴሁ።...
                      </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i10">
                     <locus from="93r" to="96v"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT2295Sayfam"/>
                      <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        በስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ቀዳማዊ፡ እንበለ፡ ትማልም፡ ወወማዕከላዊ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ዮም፡ ወደኃራዊ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ጌሠም፡ ብሉየ፡ መዋዕል፡...
                        ነአ፡ ኀቤየ፡ ኦእግዚእየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልደ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ሕያው፡ ወወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ሥግው፡...
                      </incipit>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i11">
                     <locus from="96v" to="103r"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT2444Temher"/>
                  </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i12">
                     <locus from="103r" to="107r"/>
                      <title>The prayer, “God of the luminaries,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘብርሃናት፡</foreign>
                     </title>
                      <note>MG 59, pp. 38ff; MQ 51, pp. 199–200; Daoud-Mersie, Liturgy, pp. 244–45; Sebastian Euringer, “Die Äthiopische Anaphora des hl. Epiphanius Bischofs der Insel Cypern,” Oriens Christianus, third ser., vol. I (1926), pp. 126–28</note>
                      </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i13">
                     <locus from="107r" to="117v"/>
                      <title>The prayer, “I take refuge,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎተ፡ ተማኅፀንኩ፡</foreign>
                     </title>
                      </msItem>
